p: Finally, 60 components were detected in the rosemary essential oil, covering up to 95% of total GC peak areas ( Table S3). Rosemary essential oil was richest in oxygenated monoterpenes, such as borneol (up to 24%), camphor (up to 18%), linalool (up to 6%), and 1,8â€“cineole (up to 9%). Major sesquiterpenes were berbenone (up to 22%) and t-muurolol (up to 6%). Other compounds, like eugenol (up to 6%) and methyleugenol (up to 4%), were also present in significant amounts.
